Hi, we are AR and Mig! We have both been well involved in ECESS as the 2nd year elec rep and Co-VP student life respectively in this past year. We have also been involved in  other ECESS and EUS activities throughout the year (especially in E-Week), and will work to improve the social scene for all ECE students!
Vote for us as VP Student Life in ECESS for the upcoming year!

Our plans for the upcoming year:
- Parties better than ever!
- More de-stress with bunnies events!

- More intramural sports teams! (rn we only have 1 soccer team)

Hey there, fellow ECE students!

We're AR and Mig, your dynamic duo ready to electrify the social scene of our beloved Electrical and Computer Engineering Student Society (ECESS) like never before! With AR's  track record as the second-year Elec Rep and Miguel‚Äôs as Co-VP Student Life, we're primed and pumped to give you guys extremely memorable year.

Similar to previous year, we continue to pursue the ongoing goal of getting as many ECE student to enjoy their time here at UBC. We are here to make this fun for everyone, and want to try and include some more activities that may pertain to a larger audience of our student pool, so you guys can get to know the people in your degree. 
(P.S. networking and meeting other students also tends to be exceptionally good for getting jobs ;)

So, what is on our agenda for this upcoming year?
* Unleash the Party: Get ready to come back to party! We will be hosting two parties next year! One per terms so you can let loose!‚Ä®
* Bunny Therapy: Miguel has helped organize this event in the past and is always a great success, so we are bringing it back next year as well!‚Ä®
* ECE Hackathon: Brand new this year, part of out plan is to organize a Hackathon with prizes at the school, so stay tuned for updates on that front!‚Ä®
* Game On, ECE Style: From LAN parties to Minecraft mayhem, we're leveling up your gaming experience. Have a preference? Let us know, and we'll make it happen. ‚Ä®
* Team Up for Glory: We're also expanding our roster of intramural sports teams, so lace up those sneakers and get ready to show off your skills.‚Ä®

Let's make memories, break boundaries, and redefine what it means to be part of the ECE community.
See you on the flip side!

AR and Mig
